  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col">
        <div class="jumbotron mt-3 p-4">
          <div id="accordion">
            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-header bg-ultramarine" id="headingOne">
                <h5 class="mb-0">
                  <button class="btn btn-link" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true"
                    aria-controls="collapseOne">
                    What is it?
                  </button>
                </h5>
              </div>

              <div id="collapseOne" class="collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-parent="#accordion">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h2>MagCounters API</h2>
                  <p class="lead">
                    MagCounters API is a free <strong>REST</strong> API, meaning it will return data in
                    <strong>JSON</strong> format.
                    You can use it to obtain the best counters against a desired Pokemon, information about specific
                    Pokemons or about
                    every Pokemon present in <strong>Sword and Shield</strong> series
                    at once.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-header" id="headingTwo">
                <h5 class="mb-0">
                  <button class="btn btn-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseTwo"
                    aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                    Get Counters
                  </button>
                </h5>
              </div>
              <div id="collapseTwo" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-parent="#accordion">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h2>Pokemon Name</h2>
                  <hr>
                  <p class="lead">
                    To get a JSON list with the counters against a desired Pokemon you must make a request to:
                  </p>
                  <div class="alert alert-secondary">
                    <strong>http://www.magcounters.com/api/counters?pokemon=snorlax</strong>
                  </div>
                  <p class="lead">
                    For the request above you are expected to receive:
                  </p>
                  <div class="alert alert-purple">
                    <code>
                      [ {"pokemonInfo":{"name":"Conkeldurr","dexnumber":534,"type1":"Fighting","type2":"-","hp":105,"atk":140,"def":95,"spatk":55,"spdef":65,"speed":45,"bug":0.5,"dragon":1,"electric":1,"fairy":2,"fighting":1,"fire":1,"flying":2,"ghost":1,"grass":1,"ground":1,"ice":1,"normal":1,"poison":1,"psychic":2,"rock":0.5,"steel":1,"water":1,"ability1":"Guts","ability2":"Sheer Force","ability3":"Iron Fist","rarity":"N"},"coeficient":2,"score":431}, <span class="highlight">(... more 29 counters)</span> ]
                    </code>
                  </div>
                  <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-block p-2" href="/api/counters/?pokemon=snorlax" target="_blank">
                    Try it! <i class="fas fa-external-link-alt pl-1"></i>
                  </a>
                  <h2 class="mt-4">Counter Option</h2>
                  <hr>
                  <p class="lead">
                    You can also specify if you want offensive or defensive counters with the 'option' parameter. The
                    default value for this parameter is 'offensive'.
                  </p>
                  <div class="alert alert-secondary">
                    <strong>http://www.magcounters.com/api/counters?pokemon=snorlax&option=offensive</strong></div>
                  <div class="alert alert-secondary">
                    <strong>http://www.magcounters.com/api/counters?pokemon=snorlax&option=defensive</strong></div>
                  <h2 class="mt-4">Filtering</h2>
                  <hr>
                  <p class="lead">
                    Last but not least, you can filter Pokemons by their rarity with the 'allows' parameter. The default
                    value for this parameter is 'everything'.
                  </p>
                  <div class="alert alert-secondary">
                    <strong>http://www.magcounters.com/api/counters?pokemon=snorlax&allows=none</strong></div>
                  <ul class="list-group">
                    <li class="list-group-item">Use <strong>allows=none</strong> in case you don't want the results to
                      include legendaries, sub-legendaries or mythicals.</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">Use <strong>allows=mythicals</strong> in case you want the results to
                      include mythicals, but not sub-legendaries or legendaries.</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">Use <strong>allows=mythicals-sub-legendaries</strong> to include all of
                      the above plus sub-legendaries.</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">Use <strong>allows=everything</strong> to include every Pokemon without
                      exception.</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-header" id="headingThree">
                <h5 class="mb-0">
                  <button class="btn btn-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseThree"
                    aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
                    Get Specific Pokemon
                  </button>
                </h5>
              </div>
              <div id="collapseThree" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-parent="#accordion">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h2>Pokemon Name</h2>
                  <p class="lead">
                    To get a JSON object containing info about a desired pokemon you must make a request to:
                  </p>
                  <div class="alert alert-secondary">
                    <strong>http://www.magcounters.com/api/pokemon?pokemon=wailord</strong></div>
                  <p class="lead">
                    For the request above you are expected to receive:
                  </p>
                  <div class="alert alert-purple">
                    <code>
                      {"id":321,"name":"Wailord","dexnumber":321,"type1":"Water","type2":"-","hp":170,"atk":90,"def":45,"spatk":90,"spdef":45,"speed":60,"bug":1,"dark":1,"dragon":1,"electric":2,"fairy":1,"fighting":1,"fire":0.5,"flying":1,"ghost":1,"grass":2,"ground":1,"ice":0.5,"normal":1,"poison":1,"psychic":1,"rock":1,"steel":0.5,"water":0.5,"ability1":"Water Veil","ability2":"Oblivious","ability3":"Pressure","rarity":"N"}
                    </code>
                  </div>
                  <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-block p-2" href="/api/pokemon/?pokemon=wailord" target="_blank">
                    Try it! <i class="fas fa-external-link-alt pl-1"></i>
                  </a>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-header" id="headingFour">
                <h5 class="mb-0">
                  <button class="btn btn-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseFour"
                    aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                    Get All Pokemons
                  </button>
                </h5>
              </div>
              <div id="collapseFour" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-parent="#accordion">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h2>All Pokemons</h2>
                  <p class="lead">You can easily get data about all 695 registered Pokemons by making a request to the
                    URL below. Note that no parameters are necessary for this request.</p>
                  <div class="alert alert-secondary"><strong>http://www.magcounters.com/api/pokemons</strong></div>
                  <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-block p-2" href="/api/pokemons" target="_blank">
                    Try it! <i class="fas fa-external-link-alt pl-1"></i>
                  </a>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-header" id="headingFive">
                <h5 class="mb-0">
                  <button class="btn btn-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseFive"
                    aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                    Status Codes
                  </button>
                </h5>
              </div>
              <div id="collapseFive" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-parent="#accordion">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h2>Status Codes</h2>
                  <p class="lead">MagCounters API can return 4 types of status codes:</p>
                  <ul class="list-group">
                    <li class="list-group-item"><span class="status-success">200</span> - Success!</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item"><span class="status-error">400</span> - Missing mandatory parameter
                      'pokemon' or wrong parameters. Make sure you typed everything correctly.</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item"><span class="status-error">404</span> - The Pokemon you typed is not
                      registered in MagCounters database and could not be found.</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item"><span class="status-error">500</span> - Internal server error, in this
                      case it's not your fault!</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
